This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video inpainting, which is a task related to image and video processing. The use of deep learning architectures also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of fully convolutional networks, which are commonly used in image segmentation tasks, suggesting that it could belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a new data-driven method for video inpainting, which could make it relevant to the learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
